3. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) - The paper incorporates users' privacy into the problem formulation and proposes privacy-preserving mechanisms, which is a key area of research in cybersecurity and privacy. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper's focus on privacy-preserving mechanisms and their impact on competitive diffusion may also fall under the scope of this sub-category.
